  "body": "{\"query\":\"Playwright visual testing screenshots responsive official docs\",\"follow_up_questions\":null,\"answer\":null,\"images\":[],\"results\":[{\"url\":\"https://www.chromatic.com/blog/how-to-visual-test-ui-using-playwright\",\"title\":\"Visual testing with Playwright\",\"content\":\"# Visual testing with Playwright. Learn how to perform visual tests in Playwright. ****Summary****: Learn how to perform automated visual tests with Playwright's visual comparison workflow. Then, take this further by capturing debuggable, interactive snapshots (rather than static images) that you host and test in the cloud with Chromatic's Playwright integration. In this guide, we’ll explore how you can perform visual regression testing in Playwright end-to-end tests via Playwright’s visual comparisons. Learn how to begin visual testing with Playwright's default visual testing features. Then, discover how to take your visual tests even further by capturing interactive, debuggable snapshots at any point in a test run. Visual regression testing (or, visual testing for short) is a testing methodology for checking and verifying the visual elements of your application's UI, such as responsive design, cross-browser/device differences, localization, dynamic content, and more. To begin snapshot testing in Playwright, let’s start with an example end-to-end test that opens a dialog and then clicks the close button:.\",\"score\":0.7040996,\"raw_content\":null},{\"url\":\"https://playwright.dev/docs/test-snapshots\",\"title\":\"Visual comparisons | Playwright\",\"content\":\"Playwright Test includes the ability to produce and visually compare screenshots using `await expect(page).toHaveScreenshot()`. On first execution, Playwright test will generate reference screenshots. `Error: A snapshot doesn't exist at example.spec.ts-snapshots/example-test-1-chromium-darwin.png, writing actual.`. This method took a bunch of screenshots until two consecutive screenshots matched, and saved the last screenshot to file system. The name of the folder with the golden expectations starts with the name of your test file:. The snapshot name `example-test-1-chromium-darwin.png` consists of a few parts:. `example-test-1-chromium-darwin.png`. `example-test-1.png` - an auto-generated name of the snapshot. Alternatively you can specify snapshot name as the first argument of the `toHaveScreenshot()` method:. `await expect(page).toHaveScreenshot('landing.png');`. `chromium-darwin` - the browser name and the platform. The snapshot name and path can be configured with testConfig.snapshotPathTemplate in the playwright config. Note that `toHaveScreenshot()` also accepts an array of path segments to the snapshot file such as `expect().toHaveScreenshot(['relative', 'path', 'to', 'snapshot.png'])`. `expect().toHaveScreenshot(['relative', 'path', 'to', 'snapshot.png'])`. Sometimes you need to update the reference screenshot, for example when the page has changed.\",\"score\":0.64986813,\"raw_content\":null},{\"url\":\"https://testdino.com/blog/playwright-visual-testing\",\"title\":\"Playwright Visual Testing: toHaveScreenshot, CI Diffs & Baseline ...\",\"content\":\"# Playwright Visual Testing: toHaveScreenshot, CI Diffs & Baseline Setup. Set up playwright visual testing with toHaveScreenshot, manage baselines in CI, and debug screenshot diffs with confidence. Playwright visual testing concepts showing snapshot commands, baseline comparison, and visual diff debugging in CI. Then a user opens the page on a different screen, and the layout is off, a button has shifted, or a modal covers the checkout form. This guide covers playwright visual testing from setup to CI integration. ## What is playwright visual testing? **Definition:** Playwright visual testing is a form of snapshot testing that compares a screenshot of your UI against a saved baseline image. Here is how playwright visual testing works at a high level:. * **Every run after that:** Playwright takes a fresh screenshot and compares it pixel-by-pixel against the baseline. Playwright visual testing sits between unit tests and manual QA in the types of software testing you can do with Playwright.\",\"score\":0.644248,\"raw_content\":null},{\"url\":\"https://www.checklyhq.com/blog/screenshot-monitoring-with-playwright\",\"title\":\"Screenshot Testing with Playwright: Beginner's Guide\",\"content\":\"Read our blog to learn about the latest trends in monitoring and automation. # Writing Your First Visual Regression Check in Playwright. Once we’ve done a visual regression test start to finish in Playwright, we’ll show how you can add Checkly tools to create visual regression monitors. This includes test and expect, which you'll use to define and run your tests. Here's a step-by-step guide to writing a test case that checks the visual integrity of a web page, specifically a page about raccoons:. This function will contain the steps to navigate to the page and take a screenshot. To see how Playwright handles visual regressions, make a visual change to your test page. For continuous monitoring of your site, with alerts when visual comparison fails and easy viewer to show visual differences, considering running your Playwright code on Checkly. To see more about how to use Checkly for visual regression monitoring, check out our documentation.\",\"score\":0.5660431,\"raw_content\":null},{\"url\":\"https://playwright.dev/docs/api/class-snapshotassertions\",\"title\":\"SnapshotAssertions | Playwright\",\"content\":\"Playwright provides methods for comparing page and element screenshots with expected values stored in files. `expect(screenshot).toMatchSnapshot('landing-page.png');`. ### toMatchSnapshot(name)​\\\"). To compare screenshots, use expect(page).toHaveScreenshot() instead. Ensures that passed value, either a string or a Buffer, matches the expected snapshot stored in the test snapshots directory. expect(await page.screenshot()).toMatchSnapshot('landing-page.png');. // Pass options to customize the snapshot comparison and have a generated name. expect(await page.screenshot()).toMatchSnapshot('landing-page.png', { threshold: 0.3 });. maxDiffPixels: 27, // allow no more than 27 different pixels. expect(await page.screenshot()).toMatchSnapshot(['landing', 'step2.png']);. An acceptable ratio of pixels that are different to the total amount of pixels, between `0` and `1`. An acceptable perceived color difference in the YIQ color space between the same pixel in compared images, between zero (strict) and one (lax), default is configurable with `TestConfig.expect`. An acceptable amount of pixels that could be different. Default is configurable with `TestConfig.expect`. ### toMatchSnapshot(options)​\\\"). `// Basic usage and the file name is derived from the test name. expect(await page.screenshot()).toMatchSnapshot();. // Configure image matching threshold and snapshot name.\",\"score\":0.5013922,\"raw_content\":null},{\"url\":\"https://playwright.dev/docs/api/class-pageassertions\",\"title\":\"PageAssertions | Playwright\",\"content\":\"The PageAssertions class provides assertion methods that can be used to make assertions about the Page state in the tests. `import { test, expect } from '@playwright/test';. test('navigates to login', async ({ page }) => {. await page.getByText('Sign in').click();. await expect(page).toHaveURL(/.*\\\\/login/);. `await expect(page).toHaveScreenshot('image.png');`. Specify the color of the overlay box for masked elements, in CSS color format. `await expect(page).toHaveTitle(/.*checkout/);`. Ensures the page is navigated to the given URL. `// Check for the page URL to be 'https://playwright.dev/docs/intro' (including query string). await expect(page).toHaveURL('https://playwright.dev/docs/intro');. // Check for the page URL to match the URL pattern. await expect(page).toHaveURL(url => {. When baseURL is provided via the context options and the `url` argument is a string, the two values are merged via the `new URL()` constructor and used for the comparison against the current browser URL. Name of the snapshot to store in the snapshot folder corresponding to this test. `await expect(page).not.toHaveURL('error');`.\",\"score\":0.49362883,\"raw_content\":null}],\"response_time\":0.73,\"request_id\":\"7a61b766-c92e-45f5-836d-37433d36a37e\"}"
